=head1 DESCRIPTION

Used to configure quotas that define how much storage a user or group
can use on an FSx for OpenZFS volume. For more information, see Volume
properties
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/fsx/latest/OpenZFSGuide/managing-volumes.html#volume-properties)
in the FSx for OpenZFS User Guide.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Id => Int

The ID of the user or group that the quota applies to.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> StorageCapacityQuotaGiB => Int

The user or group's storage quota, in gibibytes (GiB).


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Type => Str

Specifies whether the quota applies to a user or group.



